\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Should not the multitude of words be answered? And should a man full of talk be vindicated? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Should your empty talk make men hold their peace? And when you mock, should no one rebuke you? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 For you have said, "My doctrine is pure, And I am clean in your eyes.' 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But oh, that God would speak, And open His lips against you, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 That He would show you the secrets of wisdom! For they would double your prudence. Know therefore that God exacts from you Less than your iniquity deserves. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Can you search out the deep things of God? Can you find out the limits of the Almighty? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 They are higher than heaven-- what can you do? Deeper than Sheol-- what can you know? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Their measure is longer than the earth And broader than the sea.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "If He passes by, imprisons, and gathers to judgment, Then who can hinder Him? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 For He knows deceitful men; He sees wickedness also. Will He not then consider it? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 For an empty-headed man will be wise, When a wild donkey's colt is born a man. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "If you would prepare your heart, And stretch out your hands toward Him; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 If iniquity were in your hand, and you put it far away, And would not let wickedness dwell in your tents; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Then surely you could lift up your face without spot; Yes, you could be steadfast, and not fear; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Because you would forget your misery, And remember it as waters that have passed away, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 And your life would be brighter than noonday. Though you were dark, you would be like the morning. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 And you would be secure, because there is hope; Yes, you would dig around you, and take your rest in safety. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 You would also lie down, and no one would make you afraid; Yes, many would court your favor. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But the eyes of the wicked will fail, And they shall not escape, And their hope--loss of life!" 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 12
\b0\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 Then Job answered and said:\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "No doubt you are the people, And wisdom will die with you! 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But I have understanding as well as you; I am not inferior to you. Indeed, who does not know such things as these? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "I am one mocked by his friends, Who called on God, and He answered him, The just and blameless who is ridiculed. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 A lamp is despised in the thought of one who is at ease; It is made ready for those whose feet slip. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 The tents of robbers prosper, And those who provoke God are secure-- In what God provides by His hand. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "But now ask the beasts, and they will teach you; And the birds of the air, and they will tell you; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Or speak to the earth, and it will teach you; And the fish of the sea will explain to you. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Who among all these does not know That the hand of the LORD has done this,\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 In whose hand is the life of every living thing, And the breath of all mankind?\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Does not the ear test words And the mouth taste its food? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Wisdom is with aged men, And with length of days, understanding. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "With Him are wisdom and strength, He has counsel and understanding. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 If He breaks a thing down, it cannot be rebuilt; If He imprisons a man, there can be no release. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 If He withholds the waters, they dry up; If He sends them out, they overwhelm the earth. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 With Him are strength and prudence. The deceived and the deceiver are His. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He leads counselors away plundered, And makes fools of the judges.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He loosens the bonds of kings, And binds their waist with a belt.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He leads princes away plundered, And overthrows the mighty. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He deprives the trusted ones of speech, And takes away the discernment of the elders. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He pours contempt on princes, And disarms the mighty. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He uncovers deep things out of darkness, And brings the shadow of death to light. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He makes nations great, and destroys them; He enlarges nations, and guides them. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He takes away the understanding of the chiefs of the people of the earth, And makes them wander in a pathless wilderness. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 They grope in the dark without light, And He makes them stagger like a drunken man. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 13
\b0\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 "Behold, my eye has seen all this, My ear has heard and understood it. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 What you know, I also know; I am not inferior to you.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But I would speak to the Almighty, And I desire to reason with God. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But you forgers of lies, You are all worthless physicians.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Oh, that you would be silent, And it would be your wisdom!\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Now hear my reasoning, And heed the pleadings of my lips. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Will you speak wickedly for God, And talk deceitfully for Him? 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Will you show partiality for Him? Will you contend for God? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Will it be well when He searches you out? Or can you mock Him as one mocks a man? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He will surely rebuke you If you secretly show partiality. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Will not His excellence make you afraid, And the dread of Him fall upon you? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Your platitudes are proverbs of ashes, Your defenses are defenses of clay. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Hold your peace with me, and let me speak, Then let come on me what may! 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Why do I take my flesh in my teeth, And put my life in my hands? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Though He slay me, yet will I trust Him. Even so, I will defend my own ways before Him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He also shall be my salvation, For a hypocrite could not come before Him. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Listen carefully to my speech, And to my declaration with your ears.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 See now, I have prepared my case, I know that I shall be vindicated.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Who is he who will contend with me? If now I hold my tongue, I perish.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Only two things do not do to me, Then I will not hide myself from You: 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Withdraw Your hand far from me, And let not the dread of You make me afraid. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Then call, and I will answer; Or let me speak, then You respond to me. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 How many are my iniquities and sins? Make me know my transgression and my sin. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Why do You hide Your face, And regard me as Your enemy?\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Will You frighten a leaf driven to and fro? And will You pursue dry stubble? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 26
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 For You write bitter things against me, And make me inherit the iniquities of my youth. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 27
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 You put my feet in the stocks, And watch closely all my paths. You set a limit for the soles of my feet. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 28
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Man decays like a rotten thing, Like a garment that is moth-eaten. 
\b\fs64 \cf4 14
\b0\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 "Man who is born of woman Is of few days and full of trouble. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He comes forth like a flower and fades away; He flees like a shadow and does not continue. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 And do You open Your eyes on such a one, And bring me to judgment with Yourself? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Who can bring a clean thing out of an unclean? No one!\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Since his days are determined, The number of his months is with You; You have 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 appointed his limits, so that he cannot pass.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Look away from him that he may rest, Till like a hired man he finishes his day. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "For there is hope for a tree, If it is cut down, that it will sprout again, And that its tender shoots will not cease. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Though its root may grow old in the earth, And its stump may die in the ground, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Yet at the scent of water it will bud And bring forth branches like a plant. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But man dies and is laid away; Indeed he breathes his last And where is he? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 As water disappears from the sea, And a river becomes parched and dries up, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 So man lies down and does not rise. Till the heavens are no more, They will not awake Nor be roused from their sleep. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Oh, that You would hide me in the grave, That You would conceal me until Your wrath is past, That You would appoint me a set time, and remember me! 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 If a man dies, shall he live again? All the days of my hard service I will wait, Till my change comes. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 You shall call, and I will answer You; You shall desire the work of Your hands. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 For now You number my steps, But do not watch over my sin. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 My transgression is sealed up in a bag, And You cover my iniquity. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "But as a mountain falls and crumbles away, And as a rock is moved from its place; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 As water wears away stones, And as torrents wash away the soil of the earth; So You destroy the hope of man. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 You prevail forever against him, and he passes on; You change his countenance and send him away. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 His sons come to honor, and he does not know it; They are brought low, and he does not perceive it. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But his flesh will be in pain over it, And his soul will mourn over it." 
\b\fs64 \cf4 15
\b0\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered and said: 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Should a wise man answer with empty knowledge, And fill himself with the east wind? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Should he reason with unprofitable talk, Or by speeches with which he can do no good? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Yes, you cast off fear, And restrain prayer before God.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 For your iniquity teaches your mouth, And you choose the tongue of the crafty. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Your own mouth condemns you, and not I; Yes, your own lips testify against you. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Are you the first man who was born? Or were you made before the hills?\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Have you heard the counsel of God? Do you limit wisdom to yourself? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 What do you know that we do not know? What do you understand that is not in us? 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Both the gray-haired and the aged are among us, Much older than your father. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Are the consolations of God too small for you, And the word spoken gently with you? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Why does your heart carry you away, And what do your eyes wink at,\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 That you turn your spirit against God, And let such words go out of your mouth? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "What is man, that he could be pure? And he who is born of a woman, that he could be righteous? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 If God puts no trust in His saints, And the heavens are not pure in His sight, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 How much less man, who is abominable and filthy, Who drinks iniquity like water! 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "I will tell you, hear me; What I have seen I will declare, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 What wise men have told, Not hiding anything received from their fathers, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 To whom alone the land was given, And no alien passed among them: 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 The wicked man writhes with pain all his days, And the number of years is hidden from the oppressor. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Dreadful sounds are in his ears; In prosperity the destroyer comes upon him.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He does not believe that he will return from darkness, For a sword is waiting for him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He wanders about for bread, saying, "Where is it?' He knows that a day of darkness is ready at his hand. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Trouble and anguish make him afraid; They overpower him, like a king ready for battle. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 For he stretches out his hand against God, And acts defiantly against the Almighty, 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 26
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Running stubbornly against Him With his strong, embossed shield. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 27
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Though he has covered his face with his fatness, And made his waist heavy with fat, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 28
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He dwells in desolate cities, In houses which no one inhabits, Which are destined to become ruins. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 29
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He will not be rich, Nor will his wealth continue, Nor will his possessions overspread the earth. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 30
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He will not depart from darkness; The flame will dry out his branches, And by the breath of His mouth he will go away. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 31
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Let him not trust in futile things, deceiving himself, For futility will be his reward. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 32
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 It will be accomplished before his time, And his branch will not be green. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 33
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 He will shake off his unripe grape like a vine, And cast off his blossom like an olive tree. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 34
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 For the company of hypocrites will be barren, And fire will consume the tents of bribery. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 35
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 They conceive trouble and bring forth futility; Their womb prepares deceit." 
\b\fs64 \cf4 16
\b0\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 Then Job answered and said: 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "I have heard many such things; Miserable comforters are you all!\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 Shall words of wind have an end? Or what provokes you that you answer? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 I also could speak as you do, If your soul were in my soul's place. I could heap up words against you, And shake my head at you; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But I would strengthen you with my mouth, And the comfort of my lips would relieve your grief. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 "Though I speak, my grief is not relieved; And if I remain silent, how am I eased? 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 But now He has worn me out; You have made desolate all my company. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf3 \up0 You have shriveled me up, And it is a witness against me; My leanness rises up against me And bears witness to my face. 
